  <article class="single-comment">
    <header>
      <div>
                  <a href="/users/typingmonkey/comments" title="View typingmonkey profile.">typingmonkey</a>                          <time>Dec 28th 2011 18:59 GMT</time>
      </div>
    </header>
    <div><p>This seems to make good sense.  The initial dead lift of an all-rocket system requires enormous power, the use of which contributes the vast majority of mission risk.  Both shuttle disasters were caused by a failure to fully contain the extreme energy release at launch.  Yet the airline industry is mature, and a very large jet should be able to replace the first violent stage of launch with the equivalent of a commuter flight.  Honestly, one wonders why this didn't happen sooner.</p>
</div>
