    <div><p>It is entirely possible to be aware of the manifold deficiencies of the space shuttle, and yet still be objective about the future of space flight.  Enthused, even.  </p>
<p>The worst thing one can do with technology is to get too wrapped up in one solution.  Especially to the extent that anyone with another idea is denounced for not supporting the old technology.  Not to say that every new proposal is good.  Just that refusal to recongnize the deficiencies of the old is bad.</p>
